Observation Details: Singing everywhere all throughout the trails

Media notes: Calls from a female type low in a tree along a trail. Prominent Yellow Warbler singing in background.

Observation Details: Spread throughout. Was conscious of the fact that 1/2/3 loop around the same tract of land to avoid overcounting. Mostly singing males, but also a couple begging fledglings. Yellowish crown, black crescent face pattern, white wing bars, chestnut sides and flanks. For those not seen, typical pleased to meet you song as well as the alternate song. Distinguished from AMRE and YEWA songs by structure and the fact that the same song was sung consistently (the other two species alternate song types regularly). Will upload recordings later.
